I think it could be in its own module, as long as the proper dependencies are in place, as SAX parse/unparse rely on legacy parse/unparse underneath.

As far as SAX unparse not being in runtime1-unparser, I think that was due to putting SAXInfosetInputter with the other infosetInputters which are used for unparsing but are also in runtime1, and since SAXInfosetInputter was in runtime1, UnparseContentHandler was also put there. 

@mbeckerle

+1

Agreed with Mike and John, it's a bit concerning that there's some missing code covereage, but not your fault, and doesn't need to be fixed as part of this PR. Looks really nice otherwise.

@sndp2693, can you fix the comment issue mentioned by @tuxji, squash and force push, and then this should be good for us to merge! Thanks!
